sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

    participant User as User / Client
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Webhook as Admission Webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Operator as Operator Controller<br/>controller-runtime
    participant Router as OpenShift Router
    participant KRBP as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Registry as model-registry REST<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant PG as PostgreSQL<br/>5432/TCP
    participant Catalog as Catalog Service<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant CatalogPG as Catalog PostgreSQL<br/>5432/TCP

    Note over User,PG: Flow 1: Model Registry Instance Deployment

    User->>K8sAPI: Create ModelRegistry CR<br/>HTTPS/6443, Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: Admission Review (mutate)<br/>HTTPS/9443, TLS serving cert
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Defaults applied<br/>(kube-rbac-proxy config, DB defaults)
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: Admission Review (validate)<br/>HTTPS/9443, TLS serving cert
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Validated<br/>(unique name check, DB config check)
    K8sAPI-->>User: CR Created

    Note over Operator,PG: Reconciliation Loop
    K8sAPI->>Operator: Watch event (ModelRegistry)
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Deployment, Service, SA<br/>HTTPS/6443, SA token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create RBAC (Roles, Bindings, Groups)<br/>HTTPS/6443, SA token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create NetworkPolicies<br/>HTTPS/6443, SA token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Route ({name}-https)<br/>HTTPS/6443, SA token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create PostgreSQL (if auto-provision)<br/>HTTPS/6443, SA token

    Note over User,PG: Flow 1 continued: Client Access to Registry

    User->>Router: POST /v1/model_registry/...<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS
    Router->>KRBP: Forward (reencrypt)<br/>HTTPS/8443, TLS serving cert
    KRBP->>K8sAPI: TokenReview + SubjectAccessReview<br/>HTTPS/6443, SA token
    K8sAPI-->>KRBP: Auth result
    KRBP->>Registry: Proxied request<br/>HTTP/8080, localhost
    Registry->>PG: SQL query<br/>TCP/5432, username/password
    PG-->>Registry: Query result
    Registry-->>KRBP: JSON response
    KRBP-->>Router: Response (TLS)
    Router-->>User: Response (TLS)

    Note over Catalog,CatalogPG: Flow 2: Model Catalog Data Loading

    Note right of Catalog: Init containers copy<br/>YAML from images<br/>to emptyDir volumes
    Catalog->>Catalog: Read ConfigMaps<br/>(user, MCP, default sources)
    Catalog->>CatalogPG: Store catalog data<br/>TCP/5432, username/password
    User->>Router: GET /v1/catalog/...<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS
    Router->>KRBP: Forward (reencrypt)<br/>HTTPS/8443, TLS
    KRBP->>K8sAPI: TokenReview + SAR<br/>HTTPS/6443
    K8sAPI-->>KRBP: Auth result
    KRBP->>Catalog: Proxied request<br/>HTTP/8080
    Catalog->>CatalogPG: Query<br/>TCP/5432
    CatalogPG-->>Catalog: Result
    Catalog-->>KRBP: JSON response
    KRBP-->>Router: Response
    Router-->>User: Response

    Note over User,Registry: Flow 3: Async Model Upload Job

    User->>K8sAPI: Instantiate OpenShift Template (Job)
    Note right of User: Job container runs:
    Note right of User: 1. Download from S3 (HTTPS/443)
    Note right of User: 2. Push to OCI registry (HTTPS/443)
    Note right of User: 3. Update Model Registry (HTTP)
